wikipedia_page.main: Lucy Faithfull, Baroness Faithfull, OBE (26 October 1910 – 13 March 1996) was a British social worker and children's campaigner. She founded the Lucy Faithfull Foundation, the only nation-wide UK child protection charity working to prevent child sexual abuse.
